OL,7,FThe Financial Ombudsman Service (FOS)
OL,8,Fsays it has dramatically reduced a
OL,9,Fbacklog of outstanding complaints made
OL,10,Fby consumers against financial
OL,11,Fcompanies and will not be knocked off
OL,12,Fcourse by the cost of living crisis.
OL,14,FAbby Thomas, Chief Ombudsman, said FOS
OL,15,Fhad reduced its backlog of unresolved
OL,16,Fcomplaints from 90,000 cases at May
OL,17,F2021 to about 37,000 at March 2022. One
OL,18,Fin five were resolved within three
OL,19,Fmonths, and she said the service was
OL,20,Fcurrently resolving 55 per cent of
OL,21,Fcases quickly.
